1. Create dynamic web project (select web.xml checkbox while creating)
2. paste all the jar files inside lib foler (for solving all dependecy) -> maven
3. Complete web.xml file, create dispatcher servelet and servelet mapping for the same.
4. complete spring-mvc-demo-servlet.xml file
	- use component scan
	- use view resolver and provide correct prefix and suffix value
	- create dataSoruce, put correct portnumber, database(create manually, username, password)
	- in sessionFactory bean, provide all the clasess in the list->value tag for that you want to create tables in Db
	-  create transactionManager bean
5. Create all the entity class (Book class)
	-  use Entity, table, column annotation
	-  create all the column
	- mention primary key and auto increment
	- default constructor
	- para constructor
	- getter / setter
6. Create HelloController
	- use @Controller on top of class
	- create method with correct requestMapping and return view name (demo)
	- make sure that you have demo.jsp at correct location
	(in demo.jsp, we are using books/list, to support this we need to create another controller mapping)
7. Create BooksController.java
	- create mapping with method
8. Create interface BookService
9. Create implementation class for BookService



http://localhost:8080/LibraryManagement/


